config: drive scheduleReload via doLater backstop when no rendering

`hyprctl keyword monitor "X, disable"` calls `Config::monitorRuleMgr()->add(...)`,
which calls `scheduleReload()`. `scheduleReload()` just sets `m_reloadScheduled = true`;
the flag is consumed by a listener on `Event::bus()->m_events.render.preChecks`,
which only fires when a monitor renders a frame.

Disabling the last real monitor takes the compositor into unsafe state. In
unsafe state, `MonitorFrameScheduler::scheduleFrame` early-returns on
`g_pCompositor->m_unsafeState` and no frames are rendered. The FALLBACK
headless monitor exists but its frame cadence is not enough to reliably
fire `render.preChecks` (and isn't in some configurations at all).

Net effect: a subsequent `hyprctl keyword monitor "X, preferred, …"` issued
to re-enable a previously-disabled monitor is parsed, the rule is added,
`scheduleReload()` is called — but `performMonitorReload()` never runs.
The monitor stays disabled. Screen stays black. Only an external trigger
that bypasses `scheduleReload` (e.g. `hyprctl reload`, which calls
`Config::mgr()->reload()` directly, or DPMS-toggle which goes through a
different path) recovers. Reported in #14710 (closed by the user-issues
bot, never fixed); the parallel Lua-config path was fixed in #14447.

Fix: queue a `g_pEventLoopManager->doLater` callback alongside the flag.
If `preChecks` fires first, the doLater is a flag-checked no-op. If
`preChecks` doesn't fire (the broken case), doLater forces a single
direct call to `performMonitorReload()` on the next event-loop tick.

Tested on Framework 13 AMD / Hyprland 0.55.2 / aquamarine 0.11.0 — both
direct `hyprctl keyword monitor "eDP-1, disable"` then re-enable, and the
lid-switch `bindl` script use case from the original report.

References: hyprwm/Hyprland#14710, #14447.

diff --git a/src/config/shared/monitor/MonitorRuleManager.cpp b/src/config/shared/monitor/MonitorRuleManager.cpp
--- a/src/config/shared/monitor/MonitorRuleManager.cpp
+++ b/src/config/shared/monitor/MonitorRuleManager.cpp
@@ -115,6 +115,23 @@ void CMonitorRuleManager::scheduleReload() {
         return;

     m_reloadScheduled = true;
+
+    // Without this, in unsafe state (no real monitors rendering), the
+    // render.preChecks event that normally consumes m_reloadScheduled
+    // never fires — so a `hyprctl keyword monitor X, preferred, ...`
+    // issued to re-enable a previously-disabled monitor is silently
+    // ignored, leaving the screen black. Queue a direct event-loop
+    // callback as a backstop. If preChecks fires first, the second one
+    // no-ops via the flag check. Fixes the IPC counterpart of #14447
+    // (which fixed the Lua API path only).
+    if (g_pEventLoopManager) {
+        g_pEventLoopManager->doLater([this] {
+            if (m_reloadScheduled) {
+                performMonitorReload();
+                m_reloadScheduled = false;
+            }
+        });
+    }
 }

 void CMonitorRuleManager::performMonitorReload() {
